reviewText: When to enrolled, it was free but after completion of course have to pay fee for certificate. why so??

The curriculum doesn't educate concept in detail without the use of Minitab.

The course is very interesting and the insights you get, though after may seem as common sense, are usefull tools that most of the people may use in many fields, BUT the use of minitab is terrible, the software costs and may not always be available. I used python to recreate the activities and believe that when taking this course you should try to translate the content into your preferred tool (python, vba, R, etc.) so you really learn how to do it.

An OK course for novices wanting to learn more about some basic concepts. Would have liked to see more active learning, such as pauses in videos to test whether I as a student really understood material at a deep level. The examples given were overly simplistic and don't necessarily cover realistic situations that may be more complex in nature. Many parts of Minitab output are ignored in lectures and only the skeleton of concepts is provided. I noticed a lot of somewhat distracting grammatical errors in lectures and quizzes; however given that the instructor is not a native English speaker it is understandable. Quizzes do not provide very helpful feedback; they simply refer to the module and don't explain why a certain answer is correct or not.
